11:47 <DarkKnightCZ> Hi, where are stored i18n strings specified in org.xwiki.gwt.wysiwyg.client.Strings?

11:50 <tmortagne> \*l10n  
11:50 <DarkKnightCZ> i mean the Strings is only an interface, so where is it implemented?  
11:51 <DarkKnightCZ> and since i cloned the xwiki-platform-wysiwyg-client, added some lines and i still can compile the project without any issues, it has to be implemented in different project i believe  
11:53 <tmortagne> not sure it's really implemented in Java, maybe it's just to expose translation and en up built in js  
11:53 <tmortagne> mflorea ?  
11:55 <DarkKnightCZ> yup, found it, https://github.com/xwiki/xwiki-platform/blob/master/xwiki-platform-core/xwiki-platform-wysiwyg/xwiki-platform-wysiwyg-client/src/main/resources/org/xwiki/gwt/wysiwyg/client/Strings.properties  
11:56 <tmortagne> ok did not understood you where searching the reference strings  
11:56 <tmortagne> they indeed come from this file  
11:57 <tmortagne> but then it's built in js to something else  
11:58 <DarkKnightCZ> yup, it's handled by GWT Constants class (http://www.gwtproject.org/javadoc/latest/com/google/gwt/i18n/client/Constants.html)

12:38 <DarkKnightCZ> mflorea: you could know, what is needed to be done after i modify xwiki-platform-wysiwyg-client? I've done some changes to the table plugin, but i can see the original when i replace the jar  
12:38 <woshilapin> has joined #xwiki  
12:40 <mflorea> DarkKnightCZ, you need to build -war module afterwards and replace resources/js/xwiki/wysiwyg/xwe folder with the one from the generated war. Replace, don't overwrite. Then simply clear cache. Normally you don't need to put any jar in WEB-INF/lib, because the java code is compiled into JS
